title: Fox flashes a Royals-Mets World Series graphic ... while ALCS is still going on
text:
Fox flashes a Royals-Mets World Series graphic … while ALCS is still going on Resize Text Comments 0 By Jake Russell October 24 at 12:18 AM Follow @_JakeRussell Kansas City’s Mike Moustakas celebrates after scoring a run in the seventh inning against the Toronto Blue Jays in Game 6 of the ALCS. (Ed Zurga/Getty Images) 
Fox Sports 1 has provided solid broadcasts throughout the MLB postseason, but Friday night, it got a bit ahead of itself. 
In the bottom of the seventh inning, with two on, two out and the Kansas City Royals leading the Toronto Blue Jays 3-1, the network aired a graphic promoting Game 1 of the World Series between the New York Mets … and the Royals. FOX calling this one early. pic.twitter.com/rcQQnlqIbu 
— Paul Sporer (@sporer) October 24, 2015 
Toronto’s Jose Bautista proceeded to tie the game with a two-run home run in the top of the eighth inning. And while Kansas City would eventually go on to win 4-3, this could have very well been a “Dewey defeats Truman” moment for Fox. sports Success! Check your inbox for details.
